            "commit": "b4d3116f44b6613a65ed259bf2f41c1eb41e2ba4",
            "subject": "LU-3319 procfs: move configuration layer proc handling over to seq_file"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "uja.ornl@gmail.com",
          "date": "2013-12-06 16:18:46.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-12-16 03:17:49.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-4287 autoconf: Improve test for proc write and read functions",
        "message": "LU-4287 autoconf: Improve test for proc write and read functions\n\nFor newer kernels the proc api has changed to using only\nseq_files. To detect this I tested the presence of PDE_DATA\nto determine if it was a newer kernel. Now in RHEL6.5 this\nmacro has been backported but the rest of the changes have\nnot so it has broken the build. This patch moves from\ntesting PDE_DATA to testing if you can call write_proc_t\nin struct proc_dir_entry. In newer kernels that function\nis missing.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nChange-Id: I96d21ae5f055d5077da69acdcc4948ec160dd63a\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/8482\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
